						<summary>

						<p>Slab standing in Survey No. 49.</p>						

						<p>Vīra-Sōyidēva, 1317 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record registers a gift of land by the king, Kotāḷuva-daṇṇāyaka, the <hi rend="italic">pradhānas,</hi> and others. It refers to Bemmusēna-bōva, son-in-law of Baṁki-sēnabōva.</p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1240, Piṅgaḷa, Chaitra śu. 1, Tuesday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1317 A.D., March 14, the weekday,</hi> however, being Monday and the Śaka year current.</p>						

						</summary>
